{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"fields":{"description":"# Derive and enforce plan-material-pin health\n\n## Goal\nUse signed pins as the single related-material validity check across every attestation lifecycle consumer, while preserving safe rollout for existing projects.\n\n## Implementation\n- Add `verify.enforce_plan_material_pins` with default false and strict enabled-mode validation. Add `_read_enforce_plan_material_pins(repo_root) -> bool` as the only read boundary for this optional key: it catches `ConfigError`, emits a structured `logger.warning` with event `plan_material_pin_config_unreadable`, and returns false. This is an intentional key-local fail-open rollout policy modeled on `mcp_readonly()`, not the general `verify.*` posture. A successfully parsed true value enforces all malformed/missing/drift outcomes fail-closed.\n- Own the nested `DerivedPlanReviewHealth` contract returned as `health` beside the existing `attest.compute_validity` top-level `{valid, reason, verdict}`. It has `pin_status` exactly `current`, `stale-pin-drift`, `stale-pin-missing`, `malformed-pin`, or `legacy-unpinned`; `enforced: bool`; and `targets: list[TargetPinDetail]`. Aggregate target status by fixed severity `malformed-pin > stale-pin-missing > stale-pin-drift > current`; `legacy-unpinned` occurs only for a wholly unpinned manifest with an empty targets list. Child 5967 extends the same contract with `phase_status` and phase compatibility after it introduces the phase manifest format. `TargetPinDetail` is exactly `{canonical_id: string, role: child|prerequisite, pinned_fingerprint: string, current_fingerprint: string|null, pin_status: current|stale-pin-drift|stale-pin-missing|malformed-pin}`. Compare pins against current narrow material to populate it; all renderers consume this contract rather than duplicating strings.\n- Add one shared `derive_plan_material_pin_health(pin_records, *, repo_root, enforced)` helper in `attest.py`. It accepts parsed signed-manifest pins or the equivalent review-time sidecar records, treats an absent record set as `legacy-unpinned`, resolves current target states, and returns the contract above without requiring a certified attestation. `compute_validity` invokes it after signature and plan-review-kind verification. The re-sign recovery invokes it on sidecar records as described below. Malformed record syntax is data, not an exception at these consumer boundaries.\n- When enabled, drift, malformed pins, or a deleted/missing pinned target invalidate the attestation. Archived targets remain readable. When disabled, report the same observations as advisory while `valid` remains true. Treat a wholly unpinned legacy attestation or pre-feature sidecar as valid in either mode. Do not rewrite signed pins when configuration changes.\n- Define `PlanValidityProfile` with exactly `DEFAULT`, `CLOSE`, and `DRIFT_REFRESH`. Extend the existing `attest.compute_validity(attestation, ticket_state, kind, *, repo_root=None, profile=PlanValidityProfile.DEFAULT)` without renaming or wrapping it. For `kind=completion-verifier` the profile is ignored and existing completion callers never parse pins. Migrate claim-gate and idempotent-reuse validity to this function; child 2bbd later wires `CLOSE` into `transition_close`, while child cb6b owns audit and UI rendering calls. `DEFAULT` runs every existing check including code freshness. `CLOSE` and `DRIFT_REFRESH` deliberately share one rule in this storyâ€”disable only code freshnessâ€”but remain distinct call-site intents so later close policy cannot silently change progressive refresh. Every other existing check, including reopen, signature, registry, own material, and configured pins, remains active. Child 5967 later adds phase compatibility to all profiles.\n- In `drift_refresh_candidate`, call `compute_validity(kind=plan-review, profile=DRIFT_REFRESH)` on the verified attestation result. Remove the redundant inline signature, kind, registry, and own-material guards; an invalid result returns `None` before the probe. After a valid result, retain only dependency extraction/nonempty validation and the current-versus-signed dependency-hash comparison that proves code drift exists. This intentionally makes a reopen deny progressive refresh, matching all other plan-review validity consumers.\n- After signature certification and plan-review-kind validation, parse pins and build `DerivedPlanReviewHealth` before all reopen, registry, code, and own-material early returns; every such plan-review return includes `health`. Malformed pin syntax returns `malformed-pin` immediately. Otherwise existing verdict precedence is preserved, with health exposing simultaneous pin drift. When enforcement alone causes invalidity, verdict equals `stale-pin-drift`, `stale-pin-missing`, or `malformed-pin`; disabled enforcement keeps `verdict=certified` and exposes advisory health. Completion-verifier results retain their existing shape and omit health. Adding health to plan-review results is an additive internal interface change; all in-repo callers must use named keys/tolerate extras. Rollback removes the additive health key and its consumers; no stored-data migration is required.\n- Extend the `REVIEW_RESULT` sidecar payload with the exact review-time `PlanRelationSnapshot.related_material` records already collected before the LLM by child acaf. The sidecar builder validates and preserves these as `reviewed_related_material`; older sidecars omit the field and remain legacy-unpinned. This gives failed-sign recovery the related-material baseline actually reviewed without fabricating a certified attestation.\n- `resign_plan_review` does not call `compute_validity`, because its primary recovery case has no certified attestation. It retains its existing sidecar verdict and own-material-fingerprint guards, reads `reviewed_related_material`, and invokes `derive_plan_material_pin_health` on those records before signing. With enforcement enabled, stale drift, missing targets, or malformed records refuse re-sign; with enforcement disabled they remain advisory and re-sign proceeds. A pre-feature sidecar without records follows legacy-unpinned compatibility. Normal `sign_plan_review` still emits the complete current pin set as owned by child acaf.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Enabled pin drift invalidates the claim consumer.\n- [ ] Enabled pin drift prevents idempotent attestation reuse.\n- [ ] Enabled pin drift prevents progressive drift refresh.\n- [ ] Enabled pin drift in review-time sidecar records prevents re-sign.\n- [ ] Failed-sign recovery succeeds without an existing certified attestation when own material and review-time related material remain current.\n- [ ] Re-sign preserves the existing own-material staleness guard and never passes a sidecar payload to `compute_validity`.\n- [ ] Review sidecars persist the exact pre-LLM `related_material` snapshot; pre-feature sidecars behave as legacy-unpinned.\n- [ ] Derived health reports enabled pin drift as invalid.\n- [ ] Disabled enforcement reports the same drift as advisory without changing valid.\n- [ ] Legacy unpinned attestations remain valid across configuration toggles.\n- [ ] Unreadable optional enforcement configuration returns false and emits the exact structured warning without raising.\n- [ ] `verify.enforce_plan_material_pins=true` leaves new pin emission enabled.\n- [ ] `verify.enforce_plan_material_pins=false` leaves new pin emission enabled.\n- [ ] Missing or deleted targets produce `stale-pin-missing`.\n- [ ] Archived readable targets compare normally.\n- [ ] Duplicate role-plus-ID pins produce `malformed-pin`.\n- [ ] Re-enabling enforcement immediately invalidates existing drifted pins.\n- [ ] No warning event is persisted in the ticket event store for derived health; advisory state is exposed through the returned health contract and child cb6b surfaces.\n- [ ] Malformed manifest or sidecar pin metadata returns malformed/invalid at every consumer without raising.\n- [ ] `drift_refresh_candidate` delegates signature, kind, reopen, registry, own-material, and pin validity to `compute_validity(DRIFT_REFRESH)` and retains only dependency-hash drift qualification.\n- [ ] Reopened attestations are not progressive-refresh candidates.\n- [ ] `DEFAULT` preserves existing claim and reuse behavior when pins are current or legacy-unpinned.\n- [ ] `CLOSE` and `DRIFT_REFRESH` each disable only code freshness in this story and remain separately selected by their owning call sites.\n- [ ] Existing plan-review validity keys retain their values with additive health, and completion-verifier return shape remains unchanged.\n\n## Verification\n- Run focused attestation invalidation, reuse, drift-refresh, re-sign, sidecar compatibility, structured-config-warning, and config-golden tests.\n- Run `pytest -q tests/unit/test_attestation_invalidation.py tests/unit/test_plan_review_resign.py tests/unit/test_plan_review_sidecar.py`.\n- Run `make check` and the non-integration test suite.\n"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784543084768343001,"uuid":"e4e58139-ff40-4976-a8d8-2d60c164c68d"}